132  def update_gui(self, data: JointState):
133  """Update loop for the GUI, linked with the motor controller's translated topic messages
134 
135  Args:
136  data (JointState): current joint angles in degrees and velocities
137  """
138  # Force lower refresh rate
139  if (self.lastTimeFeedback + rospy.Duration(10 / FEEDBACK_CALLBACK_FREQUENCY) > rospy.Time.now()):
140  return
141 
142  self.lastTimeFeedback = rospy.Time.now()
143 
144  # Update joint velocities
145  index: int = 0
146  for qbutton in self.curr_vel_objects:
147  # rospy.loginfo("Index:" + str(index))
148  qbutton.setValue(data.velocity[index])
149  index += 1
150 
151  # Update joint angles in degrees
152  index = 0
153  for qbutton in self.curr_angle_objects:
154  # rospy.loginfo("Index " + str(index) + " : " + str(data.position[index]))
155  qbutton.setValue(data.position[index])
156  index += 1

159  def update_gui_info_control(self, data: GuiInfo):
160  """Update the current movement mode and current joint controlled to the GUI
161 
162  Args:
163  data (GuiInfo): current movement mode and current joint controlled
164  """
165  # Joint movement mode
166  if data.current_mode == 0:
167  self.mode_checkbox_joint.setChecked(False)
168  self.mode_checkbox_cartesian.setChecked(True)
169  self.curr_joint.setDisabled(False)
170  # Cartesian movement mode
171  elif data.current_mode == 1:
172  self.mode_checkbox_joint.setChecked(True)
173  self.mode_checkbox_cartesian.setChecked(False)
174  self.curr_joint.setDisabled(True)
175 
176  # Joint controlled
177  self.curr_joint.setValue(data.current_joint)

190  def calib_btn_callback(self, joint_index: int, limit_type: str):
191  """Change the joint limits for the new value entered in the GUI
192 
193  Args:
194  joint_index (int): Which joint's limits are changed
195  limit_type (str): If the min limit or max limit is changed
196  """
197  raw_angle: float = 0.0
198  # The position of joint 1 is the difference in position between the first two motors
199  if joint_index == 1:
200  raw_angle = self.raw_angles[0] - self.raw_angles[1]
201  # The position of joint 2 is the average in position of the first two motors
202  elif joint_index == 2:
203  raw_angle = (self.raw_angles[0] + self.raw_angles[1]) / 2
204  # The position of the motor can be directly taken for the remaining joints
205  else:
206  raw_angle = self.raw_angles[joint_index - 1]
207 
208  # Mapping a new joint position to an angle
209  if limit_type == "min":
210  rospy.set_param(
211  ROS_PARAM_HEADING + str(joint_index) + "/min_limit",
212  self.calib_min_objects[joint_index - 1].value(),
213  )
214  rospy.set_param(
215  ROS_PARAM_HEADING + str(joint_index) + "/pos_min_angle",
216  raw_angle,
217  )
218  elif limit_type == "max":
219  rospy.set_param(
220  ROS_PARAM_HEADING + str(joint_index) + "/max_limit",
221  self.calib_max_objects[joint_index - 1].value(),
222  )
223  rospy.set_param(
224  ROS_PARAM_HEADING + str(joint_index) + "/pos_max_angle",
225  raw_angle,
226  )
227  else:
228  rospy.loginfo("Wrong limit type in calibration callback call")
229 
230  def getRawAngle(self, data: JointState):
231  """Get the raw positions of the motors from the dynamixels
232 
233  Args:
234  data (JointState): raw position of the motors
235  """
236  if (
237  self.lastTimeFeedback + rospy.Duration(10 / FEEDBACK_CALLBACK_FREQUENCY)
238  > rospy.Time.now()
239  ):
240  return
241  self.lastTimeFeedback = rospy.Time.now()
242 
243  #Reordering positions array
244  motor_dict = {
245  'motor1': 0,
246  'motor2': 1,
247  'motor3': 2,
248  'motor4': 3,
249  'motor5': 4
250  }
251 
252  for i in range(len(data.name)-1):
253  self.raw_angles[motor_dict[data.name[i]]] = data.position[i]
254
